{
  "texts": [
    "A higher value of β results in a more disentangled representation but may decrease reconstruction accuracy, whereas lower value of β may result in a more accurate reconstruction but a less disentangled latent-space.",
    "As a result, by incorporating the β parameter into the loss function, the β-VAE architecture can achieve a more interpretable and disentangled latentspace, which may improve the model generalisation ability.",
    "The β-VAE architecture is adapted from Ref. 25.",
    "The encoder is used to generate the temporal modes for the latent-space representation using the mean vector for each time step r(t) = μ(t).",
    "The mean vectors are generated by applying the encoder E to each input timestep: μðtÞ,σðtÞ = EðxðtÞÞ."
  ]
}